			<h2 text-align="center" style = "border-left: 6px solid red; color:#696969; background-color: lightgrey; font-weight:Bold;">Break The Circle</h2>
				<h3 style="text-align:center">Event Description and Rules</h3>
				<hr>
			<div style="overflow:scroll; height: 600px;">
				<p>Photography Enthusiasts,<br /><br /><br />Buckle up!<br /><br /><br />Islamic University of Technology Photographic Society (IUTPS) is back with its yearly event. Following the legacy, &ldquo;Break The Circle - Season VII&rdquo; comes this year, promising talented young minds of the world a grand stepping stone towards the future. Like the preceding six seasons, this year, we aim again to unite everyone under a common platform.&nbsp;<br /><br /><br />Yes, the &ldquo;Call For Entry&rdquo; is here!<br /><br /><br />For your convenience we strongly recommend you to go through the event details and registration procedure and of course don&rsquo;t forget to read the &ldquo;TERMS AND CONDITIONS&rdquo;<br /><br /><br />--------------------------<wbr />------EVENT DETAILS-------------------<wbr />----------<br /><br /><br />Photo Submission Starts: September 15, 2017 (00:00:01 BD Local Time)<br />Last Date of Submission: October 15, 2017 (23:59:59 BD Local Time)<br /><br /><br />*****ELIGIBILITY*****<br /><br /><br />*Age Limit: Up to 30<br /><br /><br />Photographers around the world (within the age limit) are eligible to submit their works<br /><br />Participants must provide proof of eligibility in the form of a Student ID Card, National ID, Passport no or other necessary documents if required.<br /><br /><br />====| Section 1: Single Photos |====<br /><br /><br />Theme : Open<br /><br /><br />* Each participant can submit at most 5 photos in this section. A participant can submit in both Color and Black &amp; White.&nbsp;<br /><br /><br />*All kinds of HDR, Digital Photo Composite or Photo Montage are allowed in Single Photos. In case of digital photo composite or photo montage, all used Photos must be taken by the Photographers. (Proof of capture might be required if it is necessary)<br /><br /><br />==| Section 2: Breaking Story (Photo Story/Photo Series) |==<br /><br /><br />Photo Story or Photo Series including (but not restricted to) journalism, personal stories, creative/conceptual will be accepted. Photographers can use any type of photo manipulations to express his/her creativity. And all the photos should be coherent that shares a common theme.<br /><br /><br />* Each participant can submit at most 2 photo stories/series in this section. A participant can submit in both Color and Black &amp; White.<br /><br /><br />* Number of photos per story: Min 5 to Max 12<br />*All kinds of HDR, Digital Photo Composite or Photo Montage are allowed in Breaking Story. In case of digital photo composite or photo montage, all used Photos must be taken by the Photographers. (Proof of capture might be required if it is necessary)<br /><br /><br />=== |Section 3: Mobile Photography| ===<br /><br /><br />Theme: Open<br /><br /><br />* Each participant can submit at most 5 photos in this section. A participant can submit in both Color and Black &amp; White.&nbsp;<br /><br /><br />*All kinds of HDR, Digital Photo Composite or Photo Montage are allowed in Mobile Photography. In case of digital photo composite or photo montage, all used Photos must be taken by the Photographers with smartphone, tablets or pads. (Proof of capture might be required if it is necessary)<br /><br /><br /><br />--------------------------<wbr />---Submission Procedures----------------<wbr />---------<br /><br /><br />/////////////////////// For Single Photos //////////////////////:<br /><br /><br />Submit your photographs in a compressed form (.zip file) through email at: btc7single@gmail.com&nbsp;<br /><br /><br />1. Renaming the Photos :<br /><br /><br />Each photo should follow this naming convention-<br /><br /><br />&lsquo;Institution Name_Participant&rsquo;s name_Tiltle _Mobile no_Serial no.' (Title is not mandatory)<br /><br /><br />For example: 'IUT_Abid Khan_A blissful moment_+8801XXXXXXXXX_01'<br /><br /><br />(If you are not a student and you are a job holder or businessman, you will have to mention the name of that institution, if not then you may write as: Freelancer_Participant&rsquo;s name_Tiltle _Mobile no_Serial no.)<br /><br /><br />2. Resolution:<br />Must be in JPEG or JPG format, and must be at least 3000 pixels on the longer side. Minimum resolution is 300dpi.<br /><br /><br />3. No watermark or border is allowed.&nbsp;<br /><br /><br />4. The .doc File:<br /><br /><br />(No entries will be accepted without the .doc file.)<br /><br />The email must contain a .doc file with the required information:<br /><br /><br />&bull; Participants name<br />&bull; Institution name<br />&bull; Address<br />&bull; Contact number<br />&bull; Email address&nbsp;<br /><br /><br />/////// For Breaking story (Photo story/Photo Series) //////<br /><br /><br />Submit your photographs in a compressed form (.zip file) through email at: btc7story@gmail.com<br /><br /><br />Send us each photo story in .zip format containing-<br /><br /><br />1. Renaming the .zip files:<br /><br /><br />Rename the .zip file as &lsquo;Institution name_Participant&rsquo;s name_Title_Mobile no_Serial no'.<br /><br /><br />For example: 'IUT_Abid Khan_Dark Sides_+8801XXXXXXXXX_01'.<br /><br /><br />(If you are not a student and you are a job holder or businessman, you will have to mention the name of that institution, if not then you may write as: Freelancer_Participant&rsquo;s name_Tiltle _Mobile no.)<br /><br /><br />2. Renaming the photos:<br />Rename the photos as 'Participants name_Mobile no_Serial no (e.g. Abid Khan_+8801XXXXXXXXX_01)<br /><br /><br />3. Resolution:&nbsp;<br />Must be in JPEG or JPG format, and must be at least 3000 pixels on the longer side. Minimum resolution is 300dpi.<br /><br /><br />4. No watermark or border is allowed.<br /><br /><br />5. The .doc File:<br /><br />(No entries will be accepted without the .doc file.)<br /><br />The .doc file must contain the followings -<br /><br />&bull; Story description<br />&bull; Participant's name<br />&bull; University name/ Company Name (If any)<br />&bull; Address<br />&bull; Contact number<br />&bull; Email address&nbsp;<br /><br /><br />6. Each Photograph can&rsquo;t be more than 5 MB<br /><br /><br />///////// For Mobile Photographs////////////<br /><br /><br />Submit your photographs in a compressed form (.zip file) through email at: btc7mobile@gmail.com<br />(Mobile photographs include photos taken with smartphones, tablets,)<br /><br /><br />1. Renaming the Photos:<br /><br /><br />Each photo should follow this naming convention-<br /><br /><br />&lsquo;Institution Name_Participant&rsquo;s name_Category_Device Name_Title_Mobile no_Serial No' (Title is not mandatory)<br /><br /><br />For example: 'IUT_Abid Khan_Mobile_Iphone_Dreams_<wbr />+8801XXXXXXXXX_01'<br /><br /><br />(If you are not a student and you are a job holder or businessman, you will have to mention the name of that institution, if not then you may write as: Freelancer_Participant&rsquo;s name_Tiltle _Mobile no.)<br /><br /><br />2. Resolution:<br />Must be in JPEG or JPG format, and must be at least 2400 pixels on the longer side. Minimum resolution is 240dpi.<br /><br /><br />3. No watermark or border is allowed.&nbsp;<br /><br /><br />4. The .doc File:<br /><br /><br />(No entries will be accepted without the .doc file.)<br /><br /><br />The email must contain a .doc file with the required information:<br /><br /><br />&bull; Participants name<br />&bull; Institution name<br />&bull; Address<br />&bull; Contact number<br />&bull; Email address<br /><br /><br />--------------------------<wbr />------------Awards--------<wbr />--------------------------<wbr />-<br /><br /><br />Section 1: (Single Photos)<br /><br /><br />&bull;The Winner, the first runner-up and the second runner-up will be awarded with a crest and a certificate.<br /><br /><br /><br />Section 2: Breaking Story (Photo Story/ Photo Series)<br /><br /><br />&bull; &ldquo;Break The Circle- Best Breaking Story&rdquo; award: The best photo story will be awarded with a certificate, a crest .<br /><br /><br />Section 3: Mobile Photography<br /><br /><br />The winner will be awarded with a certificate, a crest and an attractive gift.<br /><br /><br />&bull; "Break The Circle- Best Photo" award: Regardless of categories, photographers will be judged based upon the quality of their photographs and &lsquo;Break The Circle- Best Photo&rsquo; will be awarded with a certificate, a crest ..<br /><br /><br /><br />--------------------------<wbr />------------ Judges--------------------<wbr />-----------------&nbsp;<br /><br /><br />The name of Judges will be announced very soon.<br /><br /><br />--------------------------<wbr />------------ Curator-------------------<wbr />------------------<br /><br />The name of Curator will be announced very soon<br /><br /><br /><br />----------- Terms and Conditions Regarding Photo submission ------<br /><br /><br />*Submission of photos exhibited previously in any other exhibition is strongly discouraged.<br /><br /><br />*Submission of photos exhibited in previous seasons of Break The Circle will be disqualified without any notice.<br /><br /><br />*Photographs that include sculptures, statues, paintings, and other works of art will be accepted as long as they do not constitute copyright infringement or fraud.<br /><br /><br />*The photograph must be the sole work of the entrant. By entering, the entrant confirms that the photograph does not infringe on the copyrights, trademarks, moral rights, rights of privacy/publicity or intellectual property rights of any person or entity, and that no other party has any right, title, and claim in the photograph.<br /><br /><br />*The photograph must not contain obscene, provocative, defamatory, sexually explicit, or otherwise objectionable or inappropriate content.<br /><br /><br />*Photographers will be notified about registration process, fees and deadlines after the result is published. If any &lsquo;selected&rsquo; photographer fails to complete the registration process within the registration deadline his/her photograph(s) will be disqualified and priority will be given to the waiting list.<br /><br /><br />*Judges &amp; curator hold the right of altering any selected images.( like, cropping, conversion to black and white, flipping etc)&nbsp;<br /><br /><br />*IUTPS holds the right to examine the authenticity of the photograph/source material in order to confirm compliance with these rules.<br /><br /><br />*IUTPS can use the submitted photographs for promotional activities, but IUTPS will not use any photograph for business purpose.<br /><br /><br />*Photos with watermarks are not eligible for submission.<br /><br /><br />----------------- RIGHT TO MODIFY THE EXHIBITION --------------&nbsp;<br /><br /><br />If, for any reason the exhibition is not capable of running as planned or any other causes beyond the control of IUTPS that corrupt or affect the administration, security, fairness, integrity or proper conduct of this exhibition, IUTPS reserves the right, at its sole discretion, to disqualify any individual(s) who tamper with the entry process, and/or to cancel, terminate, modify any photographs or suspend the exhibition.<br /><br /><br />Finally,<br /><br /><br />We believe that it&rsquo;s not us, it&rsquo;s you who can make this exhibition a successful one with your photographs. As we know it&rsquo;s not just your photo it&rsquo;s a part of your life you are sharing with us, cheers!<br /><br /><br />For any information, you may send a message to the official page of IUT Photographic Society or you may contact personally with the following persons.<br /><br /><br /><br />Abid Hassan Khan (President)&nbsp;<br />Cellular : +880-1615-222704<br />Facebook ID :&nbsp;<a href="http://www.facebook.com/abidkhan.704" rel="nofollow">www.facebook.com/<wbr />abidkhan.704</a>&nbsp;<br />Email : abid7340@gmail.com<br /><br /><br />Md. Nafis Hossain (Vice-President)&nbsp;<br />Cellular : +880-1680220286<br />Facebook ID :&nbsp;<a href="http://www.facebook.com/Nafis.79" rel="nofollow">www.facebook.com/Nafis.79</a><br />Email : nafis9481@gmail.com<br /><br /><br />Khondokar Anwar Shadat (General Secretary)&nbsp;<br />Cellular : +880-1687733506<br />Facebook ID :&nbsp;<a href="http://www.facebook.com/anwar.shadat.750" rel="nofollow">www.facebook.com/<wbr />anwar.shadat.750</a><br />Email : shadatanwar93@gmail.com<br /></p>


